The article is a transcript of a speech given by Michelle Obama, the First Lady of the United States, at a Youth Forum at the Universidad Iberoamericana in Mexico City. She expresses gratitude for the warm welcome she has received in Mexico and acknowledges the close relationship between Mexico and the United States. Obama discusses the importance of youth in addressing the challenges of the world and emphasizes the need to provide opportunities for all young people to succeed. She shares examples of young individuals who have overcome obstacles and made a positive impact in their communities. Obama encourages the audience to believe in themselves and to work towards creating a better world. She concludes by urging young people to help those in need and to use their passion and creativity to make a difference.